abstract = "A reproducible plant regeneration system for rice protoplasts isolated from primary calli has been established for japonica rice varieties Zhong Hua Nos. 6 and 9, line 02428 and Giza 3030-21-2-3. Embryogenic callus was induced from immature embryos in 1 month. Exposure of emerging calli to 3000 lx light for 10 days was beneficial in the formation of granular structures. Careful selection of embryogenic callus was important to isolate sufficient protoplasts. Nurse cells were essential for sustained protoplast division and colony formation. Plant regeneration ability of protoplast-derived calli was high and more than 2000 regenerated regenerated plants grown in the screenhouse set seed. "
